cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SI 

This paper focuses on the design of a secure, decentralized, and privacy-preserving system for IoT federated learning using mobile edge computing and blockchain technology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves machine learning and data analysis, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of mobile edge computing and IoT devices suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as another possible category. Finally, the paper involves crowdsourcing and incentive mechanisms, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
